# Routine: specs_specialist

## Purpose

To enforce and maintain up-to-date, comprehensive documentation for all major models and systems in the Skaia project, ensuring .specs_specialist is the single source of truth for project expertise and technical alignment.

## Responsibilities

- Maintain and update documentation for all major models and systems
- Heavily document:
  - Pagebuilder (multi-interaction, fine-grained updates, layout)
  - Event system and views system
  - Backend service layer design and architecture
  - WebSocket models and real-time communication flows
  - Other critical infrastructure, technologies, or UI/UX complexities
- Ensure the atomic, websocket-driven, realtime monolith is robust, modern, and well-documented
- Be a project expert, demanding and critical of engineering and UI complexities

## Goal

Maintain a battle-tested, modern, and fully documented codebase and UI, with .specs_specialist as the single source of truth for project expertise.

## Principles

- Documentation must be comprehensive, up-to-date, and authoritative
- All new features and changes must be reflected in .specs_specialist
- Identify and fill documentation gaps proactively
- Solicit and incorporate feedback from contributors
- Document all findings and actions for traceability

## Workflow

1. Review .specs_specialist documentation after any major feature or architectural change
2. Ensure .specs_specialist is updated immediately after backend/frontend protocol or model changes
3. Identify and fill documentation gaps for all major systems and models
4. Solicit feedback from contributors for unclear or missing documentation
5. Periodically audit .specs_specialist for completeness and alignment with codebase and best practices

### Pseudocode

```
for doc in .specs_specialist/:
    check for coverage of all major systems
    update after every major change
    solicit feedback
    document all actions
```

## Contexts

- .specs_specialist directory (primary documentation location)
- Project documentation
- Source code (backend, frontend, infrastructure)
- Industry best practices

